        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 7:32PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Auraria, or near
Dahlonega, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and nickel sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dahlonega, Garland, and Auraria.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
